Function: padicprec
Section: conversions
C-Name: gppadicprec
Prototype: GG
Help: padicprec(x,p): absolute p-adic precision of object x.
Doc: absolute $p$-adic precision of the object $x$. This is the minimum
 precision of the components of $x$. The result is \tet{+oo}
 if $x$ is an exact object.
 \bprog
 ? padicprec((1 + O(2^5)) * x + (2 + O(2^4)), 2)
 %1 = 4
 ? padicprec(x + 2, 2)
 %2 = +oo
 @eprog
Variant: Also available is
 \fun{long}{padicprec}{GEN x, GEN p}, which returns \tet{LONG_MAX} if $x = 0$
 and the $p$-adic precision as a \kbd{long} integer.
